# Security

- No secrets in source or commits.
- CSP enforced; document any relaxation with a ticket.
- `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` requires a written PR justification + sanitization.
- User-supplied URLs validated against an allowlist before navigation.
- Dependencies audited weekly; high/critical CVEs block release.
- Auth tokens never in client bundle beyond in-memory + secure cookie.
- Use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` on all `target="_blank"` links.
See `.opencode/agents/code-review.md` §Security.